text.paragraph:
Avoid concomitant use of rosuvastatin tablets with gemfibrozil. If concomitant use cannot be avoided, initiate rosuvastatin tablets at 5 mg once daily.



The dose of rosuvastatin tablets should not exceed 10 mg once daily [


  see Warnings and Precautions (



                                 5.1
                              ), Drug Interactions (



                                 7.2
                              )


  , and 


  Clinical Pharmacology (



                                 12.3
                              )


  ].

Concomitant use of rosuvastatin tablets and regorafenib, the dose of rosuvastatin tablets should not exceed 10 mg once daily. 


  [see Warnings and Precautions (



                                 5.1
                              ), Drug Interactions (



                                 7.5
                              ) and Clinical Pharmacology (



                                 12.3
                              )].

Initiate rosuvastatin tablets therapy with 5 mg once daily. The dose of rosuvastatin tablets should not exceed 10 mg once daily [


  see Warnings and Precautions (



                                 5.1
                              )


  , 


  Drug Interactions (



                                 7.3
                              ), 


  and 


  Clinical Pharmacology (



                                 12.3
                              )


  ].
